Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report of the ProfilePage notes section design.

## Comprehensive ProfilePage Notes Section Design Analysis

I've thoroughly explored all CSS and JSX components related to the ProfilePage notes feature. Here's a detailed breakdown:

---

### **1. CSS STRUCTURE & DESIGN LANGUAGE**

#### **Main Container: `.profile-note-container`** (notesSection.css, lines 55-87)
```css
.profile-note-container {
    position: relative;
    padding: 1rem;
    backdrop-filter: blur(15px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(15px);
    transition: box-shadow 0.3s ease;
    height: auto;
    z-index: 0;
}

.profile-note-container:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    z-index: 5;
}
```
**Key Design Features:**
- Glass morphism effect with `backdrop-filter: blur(15px)`
- Smooth shadow elevation on hover
- Auto height adjustment for content
- Z-index management for layering (0 default, 5 on hover)
- 1rem padding on all sides

---

### **2. NOTES SECTION ARCHITECTURE**

#### **`.profile-notes-section`** (lines 2-8)
```css
.profile-notes-section {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 1rem 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
}
```
- Full-width flex column layout
- 1rem vertical padding, 1rem gap between children

#### **`.notes-actions`** (lines 10-14)
- Flex row with 0.5rem gap
- Houses the "Add Note" button

#### **`.notes-list`** (lines 48-52)
- Flex column with 1rem gap between notes
- Wraps all NoteContainer components

---

### **3. ADD NOTE BUTTON STYLING**

#### **`.add-note-button`** (lines 16-40)
```css
.add-note-button {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-glass);
    backdrop-filter: blur(25px);
    border: 1px dashed var(--text-muted);
    border-radius: 12px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-family: "Lexend Deca", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
}

.add-note-button:hover {
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border-color: var(--text-secondary);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
}

.add-note-button:disabled {
    opacity: 0.4;
    cursor: not-allowed;
    transform: none;
}
```
**Design:**
- Dashed border indicating "add/create" action
- Glass background with strong blur (25px)
- Flex centering for icon + text alignment
- Hover lift animation (translateY -1px)
- Disabled state: 0.4 opacity
- Uses `var(--bg-glass)` and `var(--text-secondary)` CSS variables

---

### **4. NOTE CONTROLS (Edit/Delete Buttons)**

#### **`.note-controls`** (lines 73-86)
```css
.note-controls {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0.5rem;
    right: 0.5rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
    z-index: 5;
}

.profile-note-container:hover .note-controls {
    opacity: 1;
}
